Sentencas: A composite electrolyte Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O2.9 (SDC-BCS) material for co-ionic conducting solid oxide fuel cells was prepared by microwave-assisted sol-gel technique.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-sintering of co-ionic conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O2.9 composite electrolyte

Sentencas: The crystallization, morphology, and sintering characteristics were investigated by X-ray diffraction and scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-sintering of co-ionic conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O2.9 composite electrolyte

Sentencas: The obtained SDC-BCS composite electrolyte powders distribute uniformly, and SDC and BCS crystalline grains play a role as matrix for each other in the composite electrolyte.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-sintering of co-ionic conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O2.9 composite electrolyte

Sentencas: Anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells of NiO-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9/Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O2.9/Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-SrCo0.9Ti0.1O2.55 (NiO-SDC/SDC-BCS/SDC-SCT) were fabricated based on the nanocomposite electrolyte powders.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-sintering of co-ionic conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O2.9 composite electrolyte

Sentencas: The electrochemical performances were tested at 500-650 A degrees C using humidified hydrogen as fuel.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-sintering of co-ionic conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O2.9 composite electrolyte

Sentencas: Results demonstrated that the anode-supported half cells could be sintered at 1,300 A degrees C with a dense electrolyte layer and a porous anode structure.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-sintering of co-ionic conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O2.9 composite electrolyte

Sentencas: Moreover, the single cell with 40-mu m-thick electrolyte layer achieved an open-circuit voltage (OCV) of 0.77 V and a maximum power density of 621 mW cm(-2) at 650 A degrees C.
Titulo: Low-temperature co-sintering of co-ionic conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-BaCe0.8Sm0.2O2.9 composite electrolyte
